post.title: insert entry
post.summary: Inserts archive entries for the asset specified within the request.
post.description:
Inserts archive entries for the asset specified within the request.

/rest/mp/archive-entries

parameters.name: body
parameters.description:
json representation of ArchiveEntryRequestParameter 
    {
        "assetId": 74668,
        "archive_entries": [{
            "name": "pic3.jpg",
            "size": 211,
            "archive_path": "dir3/dir4/"
        },
        {
            "name": "pic5.jpg",
            "size": 70
        }]
    }
  • asseId (Integer) - asset id
  • versionNumber (Integer) - version number
  • archive_entries (list of BaseArchiveEntryRestDto) - archive entries to insert
    • name (String) - archive entry name
    • size (Integer) - archive entry size
    • archive_path (String) - archive entry path (Optional)

400.description: This status is returned when some of this is true: 1. Asset id is null or negative value; 2. no data for insert are provided; 3. No data for insert are provided; 4. Missing name or size of an archive entry

404.description: An asset with given id doesn't exist.

put.title: change state
put.summary: Update asset external data (data that is not directly part of the asset).
put.description:
Update asset external data (data that is not directly part of the asset)

/rest/mp/assets/{assetId}/external-data

          Example:
          /rest/mp/assets/74568/external-data
     
     {
       "articleNumber": "1234",
       "articleDescription": "Test description"
     }

parameters.name: assetId
parameters.description: (Integer, Non-negative) - ID of the asset to be updated

400.description: Asset ID is not a valid positive number or the article number does not conform to pattern in settings

404.description: Asset doesn't exist with the provided asset id

403.description: The user doesn't have the rights needed or the property update functionality is disabled

put.title: set state
put.description:
Deletes asset with the given id.

/rest/mp/assets/{assetId}/state

      Example:
      /rest/mp/assets/74568/state
  
         {
            "state": "DELETED",
            "variantsHandler": {
                 "type": "TRANSFER_VARIANTS",
                 "transferToAssetId": 74569
            }
         }

parameters.name: assetId
parameters.description: (Integer, non-negative) the id of asset to be removed.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description:
(Required) The required state change. JSON representation AssetStateChangeRestDto
  • state - (Required) The new state of the asset.
    • DELETED - delete the asset
  • variantsHandler - (Optional) The strategy for handling the deleted asset's variants when DELETED state is requested. When missing, UNASSIGN_VARIANTS will be assumed.
    • type - String, one of:
      • TRANSFER_VARIANTS - all variants will be transferred to the asset specified by transferToAssetId
      • UNASSIGN_VARIANTS - all variants will be unassigned
      • DELETE_VARIANTS - all variants that the user has access to will be deleted
    • transferToAssetId - Integer, Non-negative. The ID of the asset to which the deleted asset's variants will be transfered. Required only when TRANSFER_VARIANTS type is selected.

404.description: Asset with the given ID does not exist. The asset with transferToAssetId is requried but does not exist.

403.description: User is not allowed to delete this asset. User can not transfer variants from this asset to the one specified by transferToAssetId.

400.description: Asset ID is missing or is a negative integer. stateChange or state are missing.  transferToAssetId is required and is missing or is a negative number.

409.description: Asset specified by transferToAssetId is variant
